Job Description:
Under the direction of the Director of Development Review or his/her designee, this individual will provide policy review, planning, and design review for the Development Review Department of the Boston Planning and Development Agency (BPDA).
 
The BPDA's Development Review Department facilitates the review of small and large scale development projects, pursuant to Article 80 of the Boston Zoning Code. Led by a team of Project Management staff, this department coordinates with BPDA Planning & Urban Design staff, City Agencies, elected officials and the community to foster responsible development in the neighborhoods and the Downtown.
The selected candidate will work with this team. 
 
The team's primary activities include:
Reviewing proposals and facilitating evaluation of design, density, use, and physical and social impacts for development projects in the City. This review process is a vital part of shaping the use, character, and design qualities of buildings and infrastructure in the city;
Assemble and work closely with Planners and Urban Design staff, relevant City Agencies and the community to ensure that the impacts of each project are identified and mitigated and that the design of the project is one that relates to and enhances the surrounding area;
Advancing policy review goals, and Advocating for City goals and aspirations with partners at state and federal agencies.

PRIMARY ROLES AND RESPONSIBILITIES:
Provide written analysis for development projects in the Article 80 large and small-project review processes, interdepartmental planning efforts, interagency initiatives, and transportation/environmental studies;
Provide analysis of BPDA policy programs and analysis to support reforms to BPDA policies;
Attend staff, interagency, and public meetings and review sessions.
Create graphics for internal presentations and public involvement meetings using PowerPoint; and
Proofread documents for grammatical errors, flow, and formatting.

QUALIFICATIONS:
Interest in public policy, urban planning, and urban real estate development;
Excellent written and communications skills;
Familiarity with the Microsoft Office Suite, specifically Word, Excel, and PowerPoint;
Familiarity with one or multiple engineering or design programs, such as AutoCAD, Civil3D, SketchUp, or Adobe InDesign (a plus);
Past experience with public policy, real estate, or urban planning a plus;
Able to work in fast paced environment; and
Commitment to multicultural working environment.


Nathan, co-op Sp 19. In this position, you will get extensive hands-on experience with community engagement, political administration, city planning, and policy formation. As the first co-op for the development review unit, I had the chance to assist in planning and leading over 30 community meetings to solicit public feedback on developments. I was also able to draft official BPDA correspondence with City and State agencies and write memos approving development projects. In addition, because of the collaborative nature of the BPDA, I was also able to collaborate with other units of the agency (including transportation planning and urban design) on projects that I had an interest in.

