BTD Policy and Planning Co-Op
 
BTD Policy and Planning Efforts:
 
The selected co-op will be a part of the Boston Transportation Department's Policy and Planning Division, working on efforts related to the BTD Transit Team and BTD's Vision Zero initiatives. 
 
BTD's Transit Team is responsible for implementation of public transportation projects in the City of Boston - focusing on bus priority projects but also working on subway, rail, ferry, and shuttle initiatives. The Transit Team develops overall policy, collaborates with advocacy and neighborhood groups, and works with city and state agencies to advance Boston's public transportation agenda. The Transit Team works closely with the MBTA and other departments and agencies to implement priority transit projects for the City of Boston.
 
BTD's Vision Zero is the City of Boston's commitment to focus resources on proven strategies to eliminate fatal and serious traffic crashes in the city by 2030. The City of Boston's Vision Zero Program is inspired by the belief that even one fatality is too many. 
 
BTD Policy & Planning Division Co-Op Overview
 
The selected co-op will work with both the BTD Transit Team and the Vision Zero efforts. Under the direction of the BTD Transit Director, or his/her designee, this individual will provide policy review, civil engineering and transportation planning support, and assist in implementation for BTD Transit Team and Vision Zero priorities. 
 
The position requires an understanding of the pressing need for action and patience in an environment where needs, resources, and opportunities vary enormously. The candidate should have a strong interest in civil engineering, transit planning, urban public policy, and have an action-oriented outlook. The selected candidate will work with a dynamic team at BTD and collaborate closely with other City of Boston agencies - including the Public Works Department, Boston Planning and Development Agency, and Mayor's Office - to advance initiatives. The individual will also work frequently with state agencies, such as the MBTA and MassDOT, private-sector consultants, and community organizations.
 
The selected co-op will develop skills in roadway design, policy analysis, bus transit standards (lane and curbside management, bus stop placement technical requirements, and traffic signals), gain a comprehensive understanding of City of Boston transportation policy, and gain an understanding of community/stakeholder engagement.
 
Primary Role Responsibilities
 
The Transit Team Co-Op's primary activities will include:  
 
Assisting the Transit Team in the implementation of the City of Boston's overall public transportation agenda including managing project-based community processes using digital, in-person, and on-the-ground (tactical) engagement;
Developing transit initiatives focusing on the city's right-of-way, such as transit-only lanes, bus stops and amenities, and transit signal priority with emphasis on improving service to underserved neighborhoods;
Providing written analysis for transit planning initiatives, interdepartmental planning efforts, interagency initiatives, and transportation/environmental studies; 
Creating graphics for internal presentations and public involvement meetings using PowerPoint;
Providing analysis of BTD policy programs and analysis to support improvements to BTD policies;
Develops strategies to implement Go Boston 2030Rapid Bus and Urban Rail projects;
Contribute to web content regarding the Transit Team;
Proofread documents for grammatical errors, flow, and formatting; and
Attend staff, interagency, and public meetings and review sessions.
 
Qualifications:
Currently enrolled in a college or graduate degree program;
Interest in civil engineering, transportation planning, and/or public policy; 
Excellent written and communications skills;
Familiarity with the Microsoft Office Suite, specifically Word, Excel, and PowerPoint;
Familiarity with one or multiple engineering or design programs, such as AutoCAD, Civil3D, SketchUp, or Adobe InDesign.
Past experience with public policy, transportation planning, or urban planning a plus. 
Able to work in fast paced environment; and
Commitment to multicultural working environment.

 
